REGISTERED USERS:
  You MUST completely re-install the game, either to floppy disk
  or to harddisk. Please delete all Mipric stuff installed on
  your harddisk and MAKE SURE THAT THERE'S NO MIPRIC: ASSIGN.
  IF THIS ASSIGN IS MADE IN YOUR USER-STARTUP/STARTUP-SEQUENCE, DELETE IT.
  Enter also ASSIGN MIPRIC: REMOVE in your shell to make really
  sure that there's no MIPRIC: drawer. With valid MIPRIC: assign
  or older system/game files on your harddisk, it might be
  that the games do not work after the installation process.
  Before you delete the old Mipric from your harddisk, make sure
  you've got a backup copy of your *keyfiles* somewhere.
  Check out the documentation for more info about installing.

  Please READ THE DOCUMENTATION CAREFULLY before you click on the install
icon!!!!!!!!!!
  By the way... if you're unsure about your configuration, install as
"Intermediate User", then the script will automatically detect your
configuration.
  Note that the installation script will only copy the SYSTEM files to your
disk/harddisk. Games can be found in the other Mipric archives. If you are
a disk user, then you must run the installation script again for any game
you want to install, or just prepare one system disk and copy it with DiskCopy,
X-Copy or any other disk copier.

  Happy adventuring!
  
