CHANGES IN DOCS OR PROGRAM IN THE LAST MINUTE
---------------------------------------------
· The configuration file for InfoShell, "InfoShell.Prefs", is now installed
  to and MUST be located in the "MIPRIC:Environment" drawer. Of course, it
  is possible to specify another configuration file as and argument.
· If InfoShell does not work on your system, make sure you've started DOpus 5
  and ARexx (you must start RexxMast to enable ARexx).
· The hintbook for "The Timeless Empire I" is now finally completed!! (That's
  what you least expected, eh?)
· You must choose a screenmode with a large display height in the MUI
  version to be able to see the MUI requesters. If your type 'HINT', and
  absolutely nothing happens, the screenheight is too low (200, for example,
  is too low).

KNOWN BUGS
----------
The following bugs are known. A fixed version already exists, but this is
developer-only. I had better things to do than to re-compile all sources
thrice (MUI and standard version and then developer again), so you'll have
to wait for an update. Just by the way... the version you'll receive when
you register will have all these bugs fixed (so that's a good reason to
register!!!).

· You cannot edit the preferences for MIPRIC in the MUI preferences
  program, so you'll have to use the default settings. This means that
  your requesters may look odd after changing the colours. I fixed this
  bug in 3.17 by changing the binary, and I hope it works (if not, wait
  for the next version...)
· (No bugfix)New menu options include 'Save Default Environment' and
  'Clone Workbench'. I thought there's no need for a default environment,
  unless there are only two MIPRIC games at the moment... but now with
  all them Infocom games...
· Display bug at the beginning of 'A Mind Forever Voyaging' removed.
· ClearLine() function implemented (this wasn't done before, for it
  affected only Seastalker)
· MUI hint, gamesave & restore requesters now with enhanced keyboard
  control (now you can select an entry from a listview with the RETURN
  key - keeps down your blood pressure, not only in Bureaucracy...).
  Listviews are activated just after opening the requester (you don't
  have to press the TAB key anymore).
